{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Make revenge porn a sexual offence",
        "additional_details": "In the UK revenge porn is not a sex offence, so victims are not granted anonymity and are left vulnerable. Perpetrators should be on the sex offenders list, as this is a sexually motivated crime that leaves victims with mental health issues such as PTSD and suicidal thoughts. As a result, low conviction rates with minimal sentences prevent victims from coming forwards (Bates, 2015). This must change.\r\nBates, S. L. (2015). \u201cStripped\u201d: an analysis of revenge porn victims\u2019 lives after victimization",
        "background": "The current law criminalising revenge porn leaves victims vulnerable. Although it's a sexually motivated crime, it is not considered a sex offence and victims are not granted anonymity, nor are perpetrators properly punished.",
